10/06/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- Prime Minister Fatos Nano met on Thursday (9 June) in Tirana with Javier Ruperez, executive director of the UN Counterterrorism Executive Directorate. 
Ruperez said he appreciated the progress Albania has made in the fight against terrorism, stressing that it is one of the few countries that has signed and ratified all 12 UN antiterrorism conventions. 
He also praised the cabinet's willingness to contribute to international efforts in this respect. 
(Albanian News - 10/06/05)
